### Class Features
As a Skirmisher, you gain the following class features:

#### Hit points
::**Hit Dice:** 1d10 per Skirmisher level
::**Initiative Die:** d6
::**Hit Points at 1st Level:** 10 + your Constitution modifier
:: **Hit Points at Higher Level:** 1d10 (or 6) + your Constituion modifier per Skirmisher level after 1st

\column
#### Proficiencies
:: **Armor:** Light armor, Medium Armor, Shields
:: **Weapons:** Simple weapons, Martial weapons, Thrown weapons
:: **Tools:** None
:: **Saving Throws:** Strength, Dexterity
:: **Skills:** Choose 3 from Animal Handling, Athletics, Insight, Investigation, Nature, Perception, Stealth, and Survival


#### Starting Equipment
You start with the following items, plus anything provided by your background.

* (a) scale mail or (b) leather armor
* (a) two shortswords or (b) two simple melee weapons
* (a) a dungeoneer's pack or (b) an explorer's pack
* A longbow and a quiver of 20 arrows	

Alternatively, you may start with 5d4 × 10 gp to buy your own equipment.

#### Multiclassing
Ability Score Minimum: **Dexterity 13 -or- Wisdom 13**

When you gain a level in a class other than your first, you gain only some of that class's starting proficiencies.
:: **Armor**: Light armor, Medium armor, Shields
:: **Weapons**: Simple & Martial melee weapons, Thrown weapons
:: **Skills**: Choose 1 from Animal Handling, Athletics, Insight, Investigation, Nature, Perception, Stealth, and Survival.

### Eye for Trouble
*1st level Skirmisher feature*

A trained habit for the common Skirmisher, enemies' abilities are a book to be read and covered in red edit marks. You gain the "Observe" action, which can be used to study your opponents and learn information about them.

\page

{{descriptive
##### Observe:
*Action Cost of 10*

You study your target's movements and quickly glean their fighting capabilities and weaknesses. If the target is a creature and its Challenge Rating is below or equal to your Skirmisher level, you learn their armor class, damage vulnerabilities, and one of their saving throw modifiers of your choice. If the target's Challenge rating is higher than your Skirmisher level, you must first succeed on an Insight roll. The DC of this roll is equal to 10 + (the target's CR minus your Skirmisher level) * 2.

You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1). When you finish a long rest, you regain all expended uses.
}}

### Favored Terrain
*1st level Skirmisher feature*

Choose a type of Favored Terrain from the following list. <u>Urban</u>, <u>Grass</u> <u>fields</u>, <u>Forest</u>, <u>Mountains</u>, <u>Arid</u>, <u>Coast</u>, <u>Arctic</u>, <u>Swamp</u>,  <u>Underway</u>, <u>Volcanic</u>

While in a favored Terrain, you have a -1 to your action cost and a +1 to all attack rolls. In addition each general terrain type grants a bonus perk. This Bonus Perk gets an additional perk at 6th level.

You can choose an additional Favored Terrain at 6th and 11th level.

{{classTable,frame
##### Favored Terrain Bonuses:
| Terrain | Bonus Perk|
|:-----:|:-----------------:|
| Urban | You subtract 1 from your action cost each turn.
|  Grasslands  | Your movement speed increases by 5 ft. 
| Forest | You are immune to the effects of Difficult, Loose, and Hazardous terrain.
|  Mountains  | You gain a Climbing speed equal to your movement speed nonmagical and Difficult terrain doesn't affect you. 
|  Arid   | Loose terrain doesn't affect you and any rolls you make in order to resist being knocked prone are made at advantage.
|  Coast/ Ocean  | You have a swimming speed equal to your walking speed. 
|  Arctic   | You have resistance to cold damage.
| Swamp| You have resistance to poison damage and any rolls you make to resist the effects of poison are made at advantage.
| Underway | You gain blindsight up to 10 ft. away. If you already have blindsight, its distance increasese by 10 ft.
| Volcanic | You have resistance to fire damage.
}}

\column

### Fighting Style:

At 2nd level, you adopt a particular style of fighting as your specialty. Choose one of the following options.

You cannot take a Fighting Style option more than once, even if you later get to choose again.

Whenever you reach a level in this class that grants the Ability Score Improvement feature, you can replace a Fighting Style you know with another Fighting Style available to Skirmishers. This replacement represents a shift of focus in your martial practice.

##### Archery:
You gain a +2 bonus to attack rolls you make with ranged weapons.

##### Blind Fighting
You have blindsight with a range of 10 feet. Within that range, you can effectively see anything that isn't behind total cover, even if you're blinded or in darkness. Moreover, you can see an invisible creature within that range, unless the creature successfully hides from you.

##### Defense
While you are wearing armor, you gain a +1 bonus to AC.

##### Dueling
When you are wielding a melee weapon in one hand and no other weapons, you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls with that weapon.

##### Druidic Warrior
You learn two cantrips of your choice from the druid spell list. They count as Skirmisher spells for you, and Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for them. Whenever you gain a level in this class, you can replace one of these cantrips with another cantrip from the druid spell list.

##### Opportunisitic Striker
When you hit a creature that is unaware of your presence, you gain a +2 bonus to the damage roll. You can also re-roll one damage die and must use the new roll, even if the new roll is a 1 or a 2.

##### Thrown Weapon Fighting
You can draw a weapon that has the thrown property as part of the attack you make with the weapon.

In addition, when you hit with a ranged attack using a thrown weapon, you gain a +2 bonus to the damage roll.

##### Two-Weapon Fighting
When you engage in two-weapon fighting, you can add your ability modifier to the damage of the second attack.

\page

### Spellcasting
*2nd level Skirmisher feature*

By the time you reach 2nd level, you have learned to use the magical essence of nature to cast spells, much as a druid does. See Spells Rules for the general rules of spellcasting and the Spells Listing for the Skirmisher spell list.

###### Spells Known of 1st Level and Higher
You know two 1st-level spells of your choice from the Skirmisher spell list.

The Spells Known column of the Skirmisher table shows when you learn more Skirmisher spells of your choice. Each of these spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For instance, when you reach 5th level in this class, you can learn one new spell of 1st or 2nd level.

Additionally, when you gain a level in this class, you can choose one of the Skirmisher spells you know and replace it with another spell from the Skirmisher spell list, which also must be of a level for which you have spell slots.

{{note
###### Spellcasting Ability
Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your Skirmisher spells, since your magic draws on your attunement to nature. You use your Wisdom whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Wisdom modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a Skirmisher spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one.

**Spell save DC** = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier

**Spell attack modifier** = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier
}}

### Expertise
*3rd level Skirmisher feature*

At 3rd level, choose two of your Skill Proficiencies. Your Proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses that Chosen skill.

You can also speak, read, and write two additional languages of your choice.

### Skirmisher Archetype
*3rd level Skirmisher feature*

At 3rd level, you choose an archetype that you strive to emulate: the Hunter that is detailed at the end of the class description or one from another source. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at **7th**, **11th**, and **15th** level.

### Quick Switch
*3rd level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 3rd Level, your squat reflexes while in the midst of combat become swift enough to let you swap weaponry at a moment's notice. You can draw and stow any number of weapons at any time during your turn without any action cost. 

If you reduce a creature to 0 hit points with a melee weapon attack and hit a creature with a ranged weapon attack in the same turn, apply your damage modifier to the ranged weapon attack twice. 

If you reduce a creature to 0 hit points with a ranged weapon attack and hit a creature with a melee weapon attack in the same turn, apply your damage modifier to the melee weapon attack twice.

### Ability Score Improvement
When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th levels, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can't increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.

If your DM allows the use of feats, you may instead take a feat.

### Extra Attack
*5th level Skirmisher feature*

**At 5th level**, When you take the attack action, you may attack twice instead of once.

**At 15th level**, When you take the attack action, you may attack three times instead of once.

### Eye for Trouble Improvement
*6th level Skirmisher feature*

When you use the Observe action against a creature with a Challenge Rating higher than your Skirmisher Level, you roll the Insight check at advantage.

\page

### Favored Terrain Improvement
*6th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 6th level, on top of any bonuses gained at 2nd level, additional combat benefits are gained based on the terrain you're standing in, as detailed below.

{{classTable,frame
##### Favored Terrain Bonuses:
| Terrain Type | Bonus |
|:-----:|:-----------------:|
| Urban | You subtract an additional 1 from your action cost each turn.
|  Grasslands | Your movement speed increases by 5 additional ft.
| Forest | When you take the Hide action while using trees as cover, you have a +5 to the Stealth roll. 
|  Mountains  | Attack rolls made against creatures standing on nonmagical Difficult, Loose, and Hazardous terrain are made at advantage. 
|  Arid  | If a creature within 5 ft. of you fails to knock you prone you can use an Interrupt action (initiative impact: 10) to instead impose the same save or check on the creature, provided it no more than one size larger than you. 
|  Coast/ Ocean  | Your vision is not limited while attacking underwater and none of your weapon attacks suffer negative effects as a result of attacking underwater. 
|  Arctic | You ignore 5 points of cold damage
| Swamp| You ignore 5 points of poison damage
| Underway | you gain an additional 10 feet of blind sight
| Volcanic | You ignore 5 points of fire damage
}}

### Steady Breath
*8th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 8th level, you can use "Steady Breath", which can be used to give yourself temporary hit points at a moment's notice.

In addition, whenever you finish a short rest, your exhaustion level, if any, is decreased by 1.

{{descriptive
##### Steady Breath:
*Action Cost of 6*

You give yourself a number of temporary hit points equal to 1d8 + your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1 temporary hit point) for an initiative impact of 5. 

You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.
}}

\column

### Spell Combat
*11th level Skirmisher feature*

At 11th level when you take the attack action, you can replace one of your attack rolls with a spell that has an instant casting time and an initiative impact of no more than 10. You do not suffer additional initiative impact from casting this spell.

### Know Your Enemy
*14th level Skirmisher feature*

Beginning at 14th level, you are no longer limited by your Wisdom modifier when using the Observe action. You learn the current hit points of creatures you successfully Observe. Additionally, until an Observed creature successfully hits you with an attack roll, all attack rolls they make towards you have disadvantage.

### Unbreakable
*20th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 20th level, all of your Saving Throws are made with a +2 to the roll. Additionally, the first saving throw that an Observed creature subjects you to is made at advantage.

\page

